{
  "texts": [
    "Machine learning is built on training data (Reddi et al., 2021).",
    "Without good training data, nothing else works.",
    "How modern models learn from and use training data is increasingly opaque (Koh & Liang, 2017; Zhang et al., 2021a; Xiang, 2022).",
    "Regarding state-of-the-art black-box models, Yampolskiy (2020) notes, \"If all we have is a 'black box' it is impossible to understand causes of failure and improve system safety.\"",
    "Large modern models require tremendous amounts of training data (Black & Fredrikson, 2021)."
  ]
}